Ahead of the Eid El-Fitr celebration, the Kwali Area Council chapter of the Federation of Muslim Women Association of Nigeria (FOMWAN) has distributed clothes to 600 orphans and foodstuff to 200 widows in the area. Speaking during the distribution at the Kwali Town Hall on Saturday, the Kwali Amirah of FOMWAN, Aishatu Yamta Bukar, said the distribution was to help the orphans and the windows celebrate the Eid El-Fitr. She disclosed that the association would soon have a foundation basically for orphans and widows which would be named Islamic Virtue for Orphans and Widows Foundation, and added that it would be with scholarship packages.